<div id="content" class="backgrnd4"><div id="right"><div id="box6"><h2 class="backgrnd12"><span class="text1">The Eleventh Conference on Innovative Applications of Artificial Intelligence</span></h2><div class="content"><p><i>Sponsored by the Association for the Advancement of Artificial Intelligence</i></p><p><b>Edited by Ramasamy Uthurusamy and Barbara Hayes-Roth</b></p><p>July 18&ndash;22, 1999, Orlando, Florida. Published by The AAAI Press, Menlo Park, California. <a href="../../Press/Proceedings/iaai99.php">This proceedings is also available in book and CD format.</a></p><p><b>Please Note:</b> Abstracts are linked to individual titles, and will appear in a separate browser window. Full-text versions of the papers are linked to the abstract text. Access to full text may be restricted to AAAI members. PDF file sizes may be large!</p><hr /><h3 class="left">Contents</h3><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/1999/iaai99-127.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">Preface</a> / xix</p><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/1999/iaai99-128.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">AAAI-99/IAAI-99 Program Committee</a> / xxi</p><p class="left">Sponsoring Organizations / Outstanding Papers / xxiv</p><h3 class="left">Deployed Applications</h3><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/1999/iaai99-110.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">Automated Instructor Assistant for Ship Damage Control</a> / 778<br /> <i>Vadim V. Bulitko and David C. Wilkins, University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign</i></p><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/1999/iaai99-111.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">HKIA SAS: A Constraint-Based Airport Stand Allocation System Developed with Software Components</a> / 786<br /> <i>Andy Hon Wai Chun, City University of Hong Kong; Steve Ho Chuen Chan, Francis Ming Fai Tsang, and Dennis Wai Ming Yeung, Advanced Object Technologies Limited</i></p><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/1999/iaai99-112.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">Last Minute Travel Application</a> / 794<br /> <i>Andr&eacute; H&uuml;bner and Mario Lenz, TecInno GmbH; Roman Borch and Michael Posthoff, Touristik GmbH</i></p><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/1999/iaai99-113.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">A New Basis for Spreadsheet Computing: Interval Solver for Microsoft Excel</a> / 799<br /> <i>Eero Hyv&ouml;nen and Stefano De Pascale, Delisoft Ltd </i></p><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/1999/iaai99-114.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">Ramp Activity Expert System for Scheduling and Co-ordination at an Airport</a> / 807<br /> <i>Geun-Sik Jo and Kang-Hee Lee, Inha University; Hwi-Yoon Lee and Sang-Ho Hyun, Korean Air</i></p><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/1999/iaai99-115.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">Using Iterative Repair to Automate Planning and Scheduling of Shuttle Payload Operations</a> / 813<br /> <i>Gregg Rabideau and Steve Chien, Jet Propulsion Laboratory; Jason Willis, University of Colorado; Tobias Mann, Jet Propulsion Laboratory</i></p><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/1999/iaai99-116.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">DLMS: Ten Years of AI for Vehicle Assembly Process Planning</a> / 821<br /> <i>Nestor Rychtyckyj, Ford Motor Company</i></p><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/1999/iaai99-117.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">Using Intelligent Agents in Military Simulation or Using Agents Intelligently</a> / 829<br /> <i>Gil Tidhar, Clint Heinze, Simon Goss, Graeme Murray, Dino Appla, and Ian Lloyd, Defence, Science and Technology Organisation (DSTO) </i></p><h3 class="left">Emerging Applications</h3><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/1999/iaai99-118.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">Nurse Scheduling Using Constraint Logic Programming</a> / 838<br /> <i>Slim Abdennadher, University of Munich and Hans Schlenker, Technical University of Berlin</i></p><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/1999/iaai99-119.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">The Wasabi Personal Shopper: A Case-Based Recommender System</a> / 844<br /> <i>Robin Burke, Recommender.com, Inc and University of California, Irvine</i></p><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/1999/iaai99-120.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">The Use of Word Sense Disambiguation in an Information Extraction System</a> / 850<br /> <i>Joyce Yue Chai, IBM T.J. Watson Research Center and Alan W. Biermann, Duke University</i></p><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/1999/iaai99-121.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">Using Artificial Intelligence Planning to Generate Antenna Tracking Plans</a> / 856<br /> <i>Forest Fisher, Tara Estlin, Darren Mutz, and Steve Chien, Jet Propulsion Laboratory</i></p><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/1999/iaai99-122.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">In-Time Agent-Based Vehicle Routing with a Stochastic Improvement Heuristic</a> / 864<br /> <i>Robert Kohout and Kutluhan Erol, Intelligent Automation Inc.</i></p><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/1999/iaai99-123.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">HICAP: An Interactive Case-Based Planning Architecture and its Application to Noncombatant Evacuation Operations</a> / 870<br /> <i>H&eacute;ctor Mu&ntilde;oz-Avila, University of Maryland and Naval Research Laboratory; David W. Aha and Len Breslow, Naval Research Laboratory; Dana Nau, University of Maryland</i></p><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/1999/iaai99-124.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">Automated Capture of Rationale for the Detailed Design Process</a> / 876<br /> <i>Karen L. Myers, Nina B. Zumel, and Pablo Garcia, SRI International</i></p><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/1999/iaai99-125.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">A Multi-Agent System for Meting out Influence in an Intelligent Environment</a> / 884<br /> <i>M. V. Nagendra Prasad and Joseph F. McCarthy, Andersen Consulting</i></p><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/1999/iaai99-126.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">CMUnited-98: A Team of Robotic Soccer Agents</a> / 891<br /> <i>Manuela Veloso, Michael Bowling, Sorin Achim, Kwun Han, and Peter Stone, Carnegie Mellon University </i></p></div></div></div><div id="left">
